    {
      "id": "RauK1pvOhJ4tMPSsU1ygN",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 14045.332758990895,
      "y": 4933.856562237158,
      "width": 512.2235717773438,
      "height": 180,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bNL",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 749381509,
      "version": 901,
      "versionNonce": 370058707,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1768490351712,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- Our server doesn't have to wait for the generation to finish.\nWhen deploying a Next.js app to Vercel, all endpoints are deployed\nas serverless functions. Each function has a timeout of 1 minute,\nso we'll loose the response if generation takes longer than that\n(it always does).\n\n- The server can retry sending the webhook, if we don't return\n200 OK. Without a webhook, we only get one chance to get it\nright. In the above example, we timed out and lost the response.",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "ewscOBfuDQ7cNRVgDdNGe",
      "originalText": "- Our server doesn't have to wait for the generation to finish. When deploying a Next.js app to Vercel, all endpoints are deployed as serverless functions. Each function has a timeout of 1 minute, so we'll loose the response if generation takes longer than that (it always does).\n\n- The server can retry sending the webhook, if we don't return 200 OK. Without a webhook, we only get one chance to get it right. In the above example, we timed out and lost the response.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "cVT5er_WeFGvCMnlz3uGn",
