      "text": "Serverless, so cheap for us + autoscales",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "75ffsQbjFNi_t3i14HEj8",
      "originalText": "Serverless, so cheap for us + autoscales",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "6X6AVr0WFUPvM0-n2BtlB",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 13272.84152748575,
      "y": -490.496337380011,
      "width": 702.4477231792354,
      "height": 160,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bRG",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1369173079,
      "version": 2183,
      "versionNonce": 1512208778,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1772485470318,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- Usually there is a token account limit on ChatGPT etc. That’s not on OpenRouter. So\nit scales well. They have much better capacity.\n\n- You can use different models for different tasks to save money or get different\nfeatures. We need to use a model in the video that accepts audio for example.\n\n- It automatically goes to a different provider if something goes down. The same models\nalso have different prices and latencies. It finds the cheapest model.",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- Usually there is a token account limit on ChatGPT etc. That’s not on OpenRouter. So it scales well. They have much better capacity.\n\n- You can use different models for different tasks to save money or get different features. We need to use a model in the video that accepts audio for example.\n\n- It automatically goes to a different provider if something goes down. The same models also have different prices and latencies. It finds the cheapest model.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
