      "seed": 436735159,
      "version": 1879,
      "versionNonce": 952535539,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1768490351713,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Therefore we'll create a service that downloads the video from Sieve's presigned URL,\nand uploads it to our own S3 bucket. Now we own the file and it won't just disappear.",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "2saqL7bp2c3CdJ866bx5j",
      "originalText": "Therefore we'll create a service that downloads the video from Sieve's presigned URL, and uploads it to our own S3 bucket. Now we own the file and it won't just disappear.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "lw8vAc4RDpMRCrSA9bMVy",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 14923.275861363418,
      "y": 5798.1875214146285,
      "width": 753.8691184303973,
      "height": 200,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bTX",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1386713017,
      "version": 1023,
      "versionNonce": 70615741,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1768490351713,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. User clicks generate\n\n2. Sieve starts generating\n\n3. Once done, we obtain the url to the generated video from the webhook\n\n4. We call our endpoint, that downloads the video and uploads it to the S3 bucket\n\n5. Now, when we want to show the file, we generate our own presigned url and use that to\nshow the video in the dashboard",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. User clicks generate\n\n2. Sieve starts generating\n\n3. Once done, we obtain the url to the generated video from the webhook\n\n4. We call our endpoint, that downloads the video and uploads it to the S3 bucket\n\n5. Now, when we want to show the file, we generate our own presigned url and use that to show the video in the dashboard",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
